Standard and Poor's Corp said it maydowngrade Ecolab Inc's 10 mln dlrs of BBB-plus subordinateddebt.    The agency cited Ecolab's proposed acquisition of ChemLawnCorp &lt;CHEM> for 370 mln dlr. S and P said there are uncertainreturns on such a large investment for Ecolab as well asincreased credit risk, with debt leverage rising to more than60 pct from 25 pct currently.    But S and P noted that the acquisition would broadenEcolab's services. S and P said it would review management'splans to sell assets and use proceeds to reduce debt. Reuter&#3;